OTN: 

  FEC:
  “In OTN, FEC uses Reed-Solomon RS(255,239). The transmitter adds 16 parity bytes to 239 data bytes. At the receiver, a syndrome is calculated to detect errors. 
  If errors are present, the algorithm locates and corrects up to 8 byte errors per codeword. If errors exceed this limit, uncorrectable errors occur, leading to performance degradation.”

  For 239 acutal data btye 16 FEC byte added = 239+16 = 255.
