Alarms:

1. OTU Layer Alarms (Physical / Line Level):
🔴 LOS (Loss of Signal) No optical signal received
Example: Fiber cut or  Transceiver unplugged
🔴 LOF (Loss of Frame) Frame alignment lost
Example: Severe noise, Clock mismatch
🔴 OTU-AIS (Alarm Indication Signal) Upstream failure indication
Example: Remote node failure → sends AIS downstream
🔴 FEC Errors: Too many bit errors corrected or uncorrectable
Example: Fiber degradation, Long-distance attenuation

2. ODU Layer Alarms (Path / Transport Level)
🔴 ODU-AIS:  Indicates upstream failure at ODU layer
Example: Higher node failure propagates alarm
🔴 ODU-OCI (Open Connection Indication) No valid connection present
Example: Cross-connect misconfiguration
🔴 ODU-LCK (Locked Signal): Administrative lock
Example: Maintenance mode enabled
🔴 TIM (Trace Identifier Mismatch): Expected path ≠ received path
Example: Wrong routing / misconnection

3. OPU Layer Alarms (Payload Level)
🔴 Payload Mismatch / Mapping Errors:  Client signal not matching expected format
Example: Wrong client type mapped (Ethernet vs SDH)
🔴 Client Signal Fail Client data lost
Example: Ethernet link down feeding OTN

