Performance Monitoring:
1. OTU Layer PM (Line Monitoring)
👉 Focus: Physical transmission quality

Key Parameters:

🔹 Pre-FEC BER:  Bit Error Rate before correction
👉 Example: If BER increases → fiber degrading
🔹 Post-FEC BER: After error correction
👉 Example: If still high → link is failing
🔹 BBE (Background Block Errors)
Errors not causing major failure
🔹 ES (Errored Seconds)
Seconds with at least one error
🔹 SES (Severely Errored Seconds)
Seconds with many errors
🔹 UAS (Unavailable Seconds)
Link considered down


📦 2. ODU Layer PM (Path Monitoring)
👉 Focus: End-to-end data path

🔹 BIP-8 (Bit Interleaved Parity): Detects bit errors across path
👉 Example: Misrouting or corruption inside network
🔹 BEI (Backward Error Indication)
Remote node reports errors back
🔹 BDI (Backward Defect Indication)
Indicates remote failure
🔹 LCK / OCI Monitoring
Track path conditions

📦 3. OPU Layer PM (Payload Monitoring)
👉 Focus: Client signal quality

🔹 Payload mismatch
Wrong mapping
🔹 Client signal errors
Ethernet/SDH issues
